data.name: Butternut Squash Soup
data.quickTastyDescription: A creamy, flavorful soup that captures the essence of autumn and is comforting on chilly days.
detailedCookingInstructions: Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.
Add onions and carrots, saut√© until softened (about 5 minutes).
Stir in the diced butternut squash and cook for an additional 5 minutes.
Pour in the vegetable broth, bring to a boil, and then reduce to a simmer.
Cover and let cook for about 20 minutes or until the squash is tender.
Use an immersion blender to puree the soup until smooth (or transfer to a blender in batches).
Stir in coconut milk, and season with salt, pepper, cinnamon, and nutmeg to taste.
